cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the construction of a DFA for recognizing a specific language of base-b numbers divisible by k. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper involves the design and analysis of an algorithm for constructing a minimal DFA. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper involves combinatorial and number theoretic arguments in proving the main theorem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper deals with the recognition of a specific language and the encoding of numbers in base-b. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) may be relevant as the paper involves the use of formal logic in proving the main theorem.
